{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/recipes/korean-style-scallion-pancakes","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Scallion pancakes used to be a favorite treat of mine when I was living in Taiwan.  My mother had taught me to make it early on, but it always took a ton of time, and it was one of those recipes you had to put away a Sunday morning for because you would make them in batches.  Well, I was over in HMart last weekend, and they posted up a really bizarrely simple recipe for scallion pancakes - the Korean version.  (I have to say, I was more drawn to the picture because they left the scallion stalks whole in the pancake - which seems to make it difficult to eat, but wonderful to photograph.)  It was equal parts flour and water, a bit of salt, and scallions.  The pancake is made in batter format, so I wouldn't have to deal with kneading any dough like in the Chinese or Taiwanese versions.  I thought - great! But the flavor nut in me thought I couldn't possibly just make a pancake with flour and water, could I?  I guess maybe...but I opted to add more.  I checked out <a href=\"http://www.maangchi.com/\">Maangchi's Blog</a>, which always has a ton of great Korean recipes on it and adapted her version along with the HMart version.  You'll see that I opted to add a dashi miso to the batter (as opposed to the soybean paste in Maangchi's blog) because it adds a nice rich savory flavor while providing a hint of sweetness to the pancake.  Anyways, the result was a pretty delicious and quick pancake to satisfy my scallion pancake cravings.</p>\n<p>So just some notes on this recipe.  If you're not too into the raw flavor of scallions, I would try to cook the scallions for a couple minutes on the pan before adding the batter.  I did that with mine for 2 minutes, but you can do longer.  Second thing I found was the batter took a pretty long time to reach that golden brown crispy color, and when you do reach that, it's very easy to burn the scallions.  Have no fear though.  The scallions get slightly burnt, but it's more of a good caramelization burnt.  Just know that depending on your stove tops, it could take 5 minutes or longer per side.  Also because this pancake is fairly wide, it may pose some issues when you are flipping it. I found some of my pancakes split vertically because of how the scallions were arranged, so if you have a big spatula, it may be useful here.  Other than that, pair it with a great soy sauce mix because it compliments and brings out the flavor of the scallions extremely well.</p>\n<h4 id=\"scallions-cut-into-5-inch-long-stalks\"><a href=\"#scallions-cut-into-5-inch-long-stalks\" aria-label=\"scallions cut into 5 inch long stalks permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Scallions cut into 5 inch long stalks</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/f44ba8e0056a110ce70d48853eff23e6/f9294/67-2.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"67 2\" title=\"67 2\" src=\"/static/f44ba8e0056a110ce70d48853eff23e6/f9294/67-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/f44ba8e0056a110ce70d48853eff23e6/90185/67-2.jpg 450w,\n/static/f44ba8e0056a110ce70d48853eff23e6/f9294/67-2.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n#### Flour, Miso, Sesame Oil, and Water Batter\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/7fd67bc5fafffc74148a6d457685837b/f9294/67-3.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"67 3\" title=\"67 3\" src=\"/static/7fd67bc5fafffc74148a6d457685837b/f9294/67-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/7fd67bc5fafffc74148a6d457685837b/90185/67-3.jpg 450w,\n/static/7fd67bc5fafffc74148a6d457685837b/f9294/67-3.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n#### Arrange Scallions in Pan\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/b74af34bcbab7865e75e2c864ffb751b/f9294/67-4.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"67 4\" title=\"67 4\" src=\"/static/b74af34bcbab7865e75e2c864ffb751b/f9294/67-4.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/b74af34bcbab7865e75e2c864ffb751b/90185/67-4.jpg 450w,\n/static/b74af34bcbab7865e75e2c864ffb751b/f9294/67-4.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n#### Pour Batter on Top of Scallions\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/e74de4bd86d1059dfd572a4316f23ef8/f9294/67-5.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"67 5\" title=\"67 5\" src=\"/static/e74de4bd86d1059dfd572a4316f23ef8/f9294/67-5.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/e74de4bd86d1059dfd572a4316f23ef8/90185/67-5.jpg 450w,\n/static/e74de4bd86d1059dfd572a4316f23ef8/f9294/67-5.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n#### Serve with Soy Sauce\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/2fca194e62079a905d71542ced34e57f/f9294/67-6.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"67 6\" title=\"67 6\" src=\"/static/2fca194e62079a905d71542ced34e57f/f9294/67-6.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/2fca194e62079a905d71542ced34e57f/90185/67-6.jpg 450w,\n/static/2fca194e62079a905d71542ced34e57f/f9294/67-6.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<section class=\"recipe\">\n<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p></section>\n<p>(Serves 2 people)</p>\n<ul><li>1 cup all-purpose flour</li><li>1 cup water</li><li>2 tsp miso paste</li><li>1 tsp sugar</li><li>1/2 tsp sesame oil</li><li>10 stalks of scallions cut 5 inches long</li><li>vegetable oil for frying</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Directions</strong></p>\n<ol><li>Clean and dry 10 stalks of scallions cut into 5 inch long stalks.  If a stalk happens to be thick, cut in half lengthwise.</li><li>In a bowl, combine flour, water, miso paste, and sesame oil into a smooth batter</li><li>Add several tablespoons of oil to a frying pan.  Turn heat medium to medium-high.</li><li>Place 8-10 stalks of scallions parallel to one another onto the pan forming a rectangle.  Fry for about 2-3 minutes.</li><li>Pour half the batter over the scallions.</li><li>Fry 4-5 minutes until onions caramelize and the pancake is dark golden brown.</li><li>Flip the pancake and cook for an additional 4 minutes or until golden brown.</li><li>Transfer to plate and serve with soy sauce. </li></ol></section>","timeToRead":3,"excerpt":"Scallion pancakes used to be a favorite treat of mine when I was living in Taiwan.  My mother had taught me to make it early on, but it…","frontmatter":{"title":"Korean Style Scallion Pancakes","image":{"feature":{"publicURL":"/static/67-1-e7c01b07a6d633e7add6ebf1ad445fbf.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5007235890014472,"src":"/static/e7c01b07a6d633e7add6ebf1ad445fbf/b17c1/67-1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/e7c01b07a6d633e7add6ebf1ad445fbf/00e5e/67-1.jpg 200w,\n/static/e7c01b07a6d633e7add6ebf1ad445fbf/1a903/67-1.jpg 400w,\n/static/e7c01b07a6d633e7add6ebf1ad445fbf/b17c1/67-1.jpg 800w,\n/static/e7c01b07a6d633e7add6ebf1ad445fbf/04253/67-1.jpg 1037w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"feature_video":null,"date":"2014-04-19","categories":["recipes"],"tags":["recipes","nomeats","snacks","korean scallion pancakes"]},"fields":{"slug":"/recipes/korean-style-scallion-pancakes","date":"2014-04-18T23:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/recipes/korean-style-scallion-pancakes","nextslug":"/recipes/brown-butter-liege-waffles","prevslug":"/recipes/dulce-de-leche-coconut-tres-leches"}}}